  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project for Upgrading and REhabilitating WASH (PURE WASH)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project for Upgrading and Rehabilitating (PURE) WASH was designed to respond to the critical and urgent WASH needs in highly vulnerable communities in newly-accessible areas within the governorates of Homs (Northern Rural Homs), Quneitra and Dara&#x2019;a. This project responds to the high level of damage to the infrastructure in vulnerable communities who, after a prolonged period of conflict, do not have access to safe and sufficient drinking water and adequate sewerage systems. This project aims to increase the resilience of vulnerable, conflict-affected communities, targeting a total of 104,000 individuals. To achieve this end, ADRA will provide a medium-term response through the rehabilitation of drinking water systems and damaged sewerage and sanitation systems in the three targeted governorates of Quneitra and Dara&#x2019;a and Homs. This will be achieved in a participatory manner taking into consideration the varying needs of men, women, boys and girls, as well as people with specific vulnerabilities. Extensive coordination has also taken place with various stakeholders to avoid overlap of activities, harmonize approaches and prioritize the most vulnerable communities.</narrative>
  </description>
